Sentencas: Herein, we demonstrate the synthesis of W and Ba co-doped La2Mo2O9 (LBMWO) nanocrystalline powder by a sol-gel process.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of tungsten and barium co-doped La2Mo2O9 by sol-gel process for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In all the compositions have general formulae La1.9Ba0.1Mo2-xWxO8.95 (x = 0-0.40).
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of tungsten and barium co-doped La2Mo2O9 by sol-gel process for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The crystal structure, microstructure and conductivity of LBMWO were characterized by X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy and electrical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of tungsten and barium co-doped La2Mo2O9 by sol-gel process for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the thermal and decomposition properties of the LBMWO gel were analyzed by differential scanning calorimetry - thermogravimetric.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of tungsten and barium co-doped La2Mo2O9 by sol-gel process for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results reveal that all LBMWO powders calcined at 700 degrees C have a cubic structure; the average crystallite size is about 48 nm.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of tungsten and barium co-doped La2Mo2O9 by sol-gel process for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The unit cell parameter of LBMWO powders increases with increase in W content.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of tungsten and barium co-doped La2Mo2O9 by sol-gel process for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The as-synthesized nanocrystalline LBMWO samples exhibit excellent sinter-ability and a relatively lower sintering temperature of 900 degrees C. A high relative density of similar to 96% is achieved after sintering at 900 degrees C which is in good agreement with the results of the SEM.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of tungsten and barium co-doped La2Mo2O9 by sol-gel process for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, W and Ba co-doping suppresses the phase transition and effectively stabilizes the beta-phase at low temperature.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of tungsten and barium co-doped La2Mo2O9 by sol-gel process for solid oxide fuel cells
